\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
the earliest Judge version in which the command was implemented.
 If no number is listed, then the command is believed to work on all Judge
 versions currently in use, although this has not been verified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Commands prefixed by '!' have been incompletely implemented (as explained
 in the description).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each command is preceded by a code that indicates who can execute the command
 and (where applicable) additional restrictions on when the command can
 be executed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The who options are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
any: Anyone can execute the command (no SIGNON required).
 Some commands have both an "any" form and a "ply" form; the "any" form
 is required if the command appears before a SIGNON line, and the "ply"
 form is required if it appears after a SIGNON.ply: Only a signed-on player
 or observer can execute the command.
 (Unless otherwise noted, these commands can be used by a Master, too.) Any
 exceptions are noted in the command description.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
mod: Only a Master in moderated games, anyone in unmoderated games.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
mas: Only a Master can use these commands; they are not available in unmoderated
 games.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
adm: Only the administrator.
 These commands are listed to be complete, but should *NOT* be executed
 by nonadministrators.
 If there is any doubt, you are not an administrator.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The when options are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
pre: Must appear before a SIGNON command.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
mac: Can only be used in a Machiavelli variant game, and only before the
 game starts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
bgs: Should only be used Before Game Starts.
 If used afterwards, game will have an 'irregular' flag set and will not
 count for any rating purposes.
\end_layout

