\begin_layout Standard
Diaries allow a player to record his thoughts during the game for broadcast
 at the end of the game.
 If the diary command is given with no options, it will default to "diary
 record".
 Options are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
RECORD: "DIARY RECORD" begins a new, numbered diary entry.
 The Judge will read until encountering "ENDPRESS", "ENDBROADCAST", or "SIGN
 OFF" (just like a normal press entry).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
LIST: When a player issues "DIARY LIST", the Judge will return a numbered
 list of his created entries, and the date and time they were created.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
READ [number]: Issuing "DIARY READ" allows a player to read an entry he
 has already made.
 The number of the entry to read must be specified (it can be obtained from
 "DIARY LIST").
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
DELETE [number]: Deletes the specified diary entry numbers.
 Note that diary entries are not reused, so it's possible to have "holes"
 in the numbering scheme if any entry but the most recent one is deleted.
\end_layout

